dataIdInfo.idAbs: The 80 California State Assembly Districts represent the geographically defined territories used for electing members to the lower (house) chamber of the California State Legislature. The current state assembly boundaries were approved by the California Citizens Redistricting Commission in 2021 following the completion of the 2020 United States Census
